<div class="pricing-page">
  <div class="pricing-header">
    <h1>Choose Your Plan</h1>
    <p>Select the perfect plan for your needs</p>
  </div>

  <%= plan_pricing_table highlight: true %>
  <%# Or use the drop-in engine partial: %>
  <%#= PricingPlans.render_pricing_cards(view: self, context: (defined?(current_user) && current_user ? :dashboard : :marketing), billable: (defined?(current_organization) ? current_organization : current_user)) %>
  
  <div class="pricing-faq">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    
    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Can I change plans at any time?</h3>
      <p>Yes! You can upgrade or downgrade your plan at any time. Changes take effect immediately.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>What happens if I exceed my limits?</h3>
      <p>You'll get warning notifications as you approach your limits, followed by a grace period to upgrade before any restrictions take effect.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Do you offer refunds?</h3>
      <p>We offer a 30-day money-back guarantee for all paid plans.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>